    A few of my fellow ES members &amp; I decided it would be a good idea to zone into a partially populated Fear Plane. As usual once we all made the SW wall the zone repopped. We died an enormous number of times trying to recoup. From 11 PM to 8 AM we pushed hard to recover our corpses and make a buffer around our single group. Of course Fear had it's way with us<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> P <br>
    I awoke Sunday afternoon and logged in. I fully expected to gather folks for a rescue mission. Instead I am immediately asked to give consent and within one minute am accepting a Rez. <br>
    IV please accept my sincerest grattitude. Your unselfishness resulted in...<br>
<br>
          ~ An enormous amount of regained experience including 2 of us re-dinging level 60.<br>
          ~ You allowed our members to raid as if we were one of your own &amp; included us in your loot consideration.<br>
          ~ Fought beyond your normal objective to allow my turn in of the Fiery Avenger &amp; Mark of Atonement for my epic. <br>
          ~ Most significantly you were worried we were upset about not obtaining enough loot.<br>
<br>
     <br>
                                              Thanks Much<br>
                                                    Macky!<br>
<br>
